Sentencas: Multi-layer micro-tubes consisting of four anode layers of NiO and YSZ mixture, and an electrolyte layer, YSZ, were fabricated by co-extrusion.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: The die designed in this study is able to extrude 5 layers around a sacrificial core, which eliminates the difficulties from the use of mandrel in processing tubes.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) results revealed that this technique can be used for the successful fabrication of multi-layer microtubes with good bonding between the layers.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: 3-point bending was used to evaluate the mechanical properties of these co-extruded multi-layer samples.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: Moreover, thermal shock resistance of the tubes was investigated by water quenching from an elevated temperature.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: The results were compared with those obtained for conventionally extruded single layer samples.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: The co-extruded samples were found to have the highest average strength and also the highest weibull modulus and reliability.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process

Sentencas: It was also found that multi-layer anode can significantly improve thermal shock resistance.
Titulo: Mechanical behaviour of multi-layer half-cells of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by the co-extrusion process
